OL,3,CDad and son died after falling from
OL,4,Cbuilding they were working on
OL,6,FAt a five-day inquest in Liverpool, it
OL,7,Fwas heard that failure of the pinion
OL,8,Fshafts in the machine's gearboxes
OL,9,Fcaused the brakes to disconnect, and
OL,10,Ffailure of a second pinion shaft
OL,11,Fcaused the mast climbing working
OL,12,Fplatform to descend under its own
OL,13,Fweight.
OL,15,FA Health and Safety Executive
OL,16,Finspector said the failure had been
OL,17,Fcaused by "fatigue".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
