OL,3,CDad and son died after falling from
OL,4,Cbuilding they were working on
OL,6,FClayton was taken to the intensive
OL,7,Fcare unit at Aintree Hospital, where
OL,8,Fhe died on 23 May after suffering
OL,9,F"severe, irreversible and unsurvivable
OL,10,Fbrain damage".
OL,12,FHe donated his heart, kidneys and
OL,13,Fliver.
OL,15,FDavid, from Castleford, West
OL,16,FYorkshire, had been working on the
OL,17,FUnity Building for 18 months as a sub-
OL,18,Fcontractor for AAI Selby, a
OL,19,Fconstruction company contracted by
OL,20,Fsite operators Laing O'Rourke.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
