OL,3,CDad and son died after falling from
OL,4,Cbuilding they were working on
OL,6,F"This included simple visual checks
OL,7,Fand functional tests of the up/down/
OL,8,Fstop switches. These identified no
OL,9,Fproblem with the equipment. Failure of
OL,10,Fthe pinion shafts in both gearboxes
OL,11,Fcaused the brakes to disconnect.
OL,13,F"Failure of the second pinion shaft
OL,14,Fcaused the mast climbing working
OL,15,Fplatform to descend under its own
OL,16,Fweight. David died at the scene
OL,17,Fshortly following the incident."
OL,19,F"Clayton was resuscitated at the
OL,20,Fscene, then transported by ambulance
OL,21,Fto Aintree University Hospital.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
